**Explanation:**

This verse introduces the explanation of the three bandhas (locks) in the context of the four breath retention techniques previously discussed.

* **चतुर्णामपि भेदानां कुम्भके समुपस्थिते** - This refers to the four types (chaturnam bhedanam) of breath retention (kumbhak) that have been previously explained.  The speaker emphasizes their presence (samupasthite) before introducing the next topic.
* **बन्धत्रयमिदं कार्यं वक्ष्यमाणं मयहि तत्** - This announces that the speaker (maya) will now explain (vakshyaman) this practice (kary) of the three locks (bandha trayam). It sets the stage for a detailed description of these techniques.

**Overall Meaning:**

The verse prepares the reader for the explanation of the three bandhas (locks) in the context of breath retention techniques. It highlights the importance of combining these practices for achieving spiritual progress. 


